org.jcvi.jillion.core.util

Class MultipleWrapper<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jcvi.jillion.core.util.MultipleWrapper<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the interface type to wrap to make several instances appear as a single one.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    InvocationHandler

    public final class MultipleWrapper<T>
extends Object
implements InvocationHandler
    MultipleWrapper uses dymanic proxies to wrap several instances of an interface. This allows all wrapped instances to be called by only a single call to the wrapper.
    Author:
    dkatzel

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      static class  MultipleWrapper.ReturnPolicy
      Since methods can only return a single return value, only one of the wrapped methods can be returned to the caller (even though they will all be called).

    • Method Detail

      • createMultipleWrapper

        public static <T> T createMultipleWrapper(Class<T> classType,
                                          MultipleWrapper.ReturnPolicy policy,
                                          Iterable<? extends T> delegates)
        Create a dynamic proxy to wrap the given delegate instances.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the interface type to wrap to make several instances appear as a single one.
        Parameters:
        classType - the class object of T.
        policy - the return policy to use on methods that return something.
        delegates - the list of delegates to wrap in the order in which they will be called.
        Returns:
        a new instance of T that wraps the delegates.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if no delegates are given
        NullPointerException - if classType ==null or policy ==null or any delegate ==null.
